metadata.description:
Afterglow Kaleido explores the variaty of organically animated shapes combined with the kaleidoscope (multi-mirroring) technique and an afterglow effect.

metadata.name: A24Z #395
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didn‚Äôt use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on ‚ÄúMagic Mushroom Mountain‚Äù

J0rdan: Wonders about ‚ÄúQuark Question Quiches‚Äù

Okeoke: Just get lost in ‚ÄúFinnegans‚Äô Flower Fields.‚Äù

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Origami #199
metadata.description:
Origami's the artist's first generative artwork on the blockchain. Whenever a collector mints a new piece, the software generates a unique piece with a rarity level. The rarity tiers define some of the artwork features such as background colour, grid density and more.

Instructions:
- Press [L] to loop/stop animation
- Press [S] to save standard PNG
- Press [E] to export high-resolution PNG

metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #71

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #71
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of ‚Äúgrain‚Äù appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.
